                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6606.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad Porfirio
                            Díaz</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Porfirio Díaz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Governor of Coahuila, at Monclova, and Colonel Carranza, here, have just
                    seized the rolling stock shops and their equipment and other property of the
                    Mexican National Railway lines here. Evidently they intend to attempt to operate
                    all the railroad and shops for the benefit of the State cause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Luther T. Ellsworth</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
